GPO => Group Policy Organization
    => centralization and security purpose we use this.
    => appliying to a specific user and also for group domain.
2 types of tools to edit the policy in GPO : 
   => Group Policy Editor
   => Group Policy Container
   => Group Policy Template
   => Group Policy Management tool
to change the policy we have to go
Run --> groupemc --> Computer configuration ---> changing the password ---> password has 1-45 days we have to change it --> next password length --> and it will change
  --> enable to disable -->Apply and OK --> This is called Reverse encryption that means it converted as "hash" ie..we cannot reverse hash.
how to edit a policy : 
  => using GP Editor
       start and menu --> hide policy --> remove recycle bin in that --> double tap --> disadble --> then signout --> and view the disabled recycle bin.
       mmc (microsoft management console) --> file --> add and remove snap --> group policy --> browse the user --> and give the ploicy to the user --> apply --> OK.
gp update /force --> important cmd in AD.
2 types of Configuration : 
    => User configuration
    => Computer configuration
changing the wallpaper in the user account : 
    => switch to administrator account --> user configuration --> changing wallpaper --> enabled --> dektop --> path copied o fthe image --> desktop wallpaper --> save
    => cmd prompt ---> gpupdate /force
    => switch to user account --> and check the changes we made.
3 types of GPO :
    => Loacl
    => Non - local
    => Starter
